Adlerfels.label: Adler Fels Winery
Adlerfels.description: Adler Fels Winery is a California winery based in Sonoma that produces over 100 different wine labels in addition to production under its own Adler Fels brand. These include private labels for various restaurants, hotels and retailers. Wikipedia

Aggenstein.label: Aggenstein
Aggenstein.description: Aggenstein is a mountain located on the border Bavaria, Germany and Tyrol, Austria. Wikipedia

Aiguilles du Diable.label: Aiguilles du Diable
Aiguilles du Diable.description: The Aiguilles du Diable is a mountain in the Mont Blanc Massif in Haute-Savoie, France. Wikipedia

Aiguille du Jardin.label: Aiguille du Jardin
Aiguille du Jardin.description: The Aiguille du Jardin is a mountain in the Mont Blanc massif in Haute-Savoie, France. Wikipedia

Aiplspitz.label: Aiplspitz
Aiplspitz.description: Aiplspitz is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Ailefroide.label: Ailefroide
Ailefroide.description: The Ailefroide is a mountain in the Massif des Écrins in the French Alps, and is the third highest peak in the Dauphiné Alps after the Barre des Écrins and La Meije. It lies at the south-western end of the Mont Pelvoux–Pic Sans Nom–Ailefroide ridge. Wikipedia

Altkönig.label: Altkönig
Altkönig.description:
Altkönig the third highest mountain of the Taunus range in Hesse, Germany, reaching 798 metres above sea level.
In the La Tène period around 400 BC, the Celts settled the Altkönig. They built a ringwall around the summit which is still evident. Wikipedia

Amba Alagi.label: Amba Alagi
Amba Alagi.description: Amba Alagi is a mountain, or an amba, in northern Ethiopia. Located in the Debubawi Zone of the Tigray Region, Amba Alagi dominates the roadway that runs past it from the city of Mek'ele south to Maychew. Wikipedia

Alpspitze.label: Alpspitze
Alpspitze.description: Alpspitze is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. At its base is the 'AlpspiX Viewing Platform', 2 curved metal walkways reaching out 13 metres over a cliff, crossing over each other, making the shape of an X. Wikipedia

Auersberg.label: Auersberg
Auersberg.description: Auersberg is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Atzelberg.label: Atzelberg
Atzelberg.description: Atzelberg is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Ausangate.label: Ausangate
Ausangate.description:
Ausangate is a mountain of the Willkanuta mountain range in the Andes of Peru. With an altitude of 6,384 metres it is situated around 100 kilometres southeast of Cusco.
The mountain has significance in Incan mythology. Wikipedia

Bärenstein (Ore Mountains).label: Bärenstein
Bärenstein (Ore Mountains).description: Bärenstein is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Bălănești Hill.label: Bălănești Hill
Bălănești Hill.description: Bălănești Hill is the highest geographical point in Moldova, with an altitude of 430 m. It is located in Bălănești and belongs to Cornești Hills. Wikipedia

Babia Góra.label: Babia Góra
Babia Góra.description: Babia Góra, or Babia hora, literally Old Wives' or Witches' Mountain, is a massif situated on the border between Poland and Slovakia in the Western Beskidy Mountains. Wikipedia

Armesberg.label: Armesberg
Armesberg.description: Armesberg is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Badacsony.label: Badacsony
Badacsony.description: Badacsony is the name of a region on the north shore of Lake Balaton in western Hungary, and a town in that region. The entire area is recognized for its wine, with vineyards dating back to Roman times. Wikipedia

Badener Höhe.label: Badener Höhe
Badener Höhe.description: Badener Höhe is a mountain of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Ben Lomond.label: Ben Lomond
Ben Lomond.description: Ben Lomond, 974 metres, is a distinctive mountain in the Scottish Highlands. Situated on the eastern shore of Loch Lomond, it is the most southerly of the Munros. Wikipedia

Bella Tola.label: Hotel Bella Tola & St-Luc - Châteaux & Hôtels Collection

Ben Macdui.label: Ben Macdui
Ben Macdui.description: Ben Macdui is the second highest mountain in the United Kingdom after Ben Nevis, and the highest in the Cairngorms. Wikipedia

Bennachie.label: Bennachie
Bennachie.description: Bennachie is a range of hills in Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It has several tops, the highest of which, Oxen Craig, has a height of 528 m. Wikipedia

Besiberri Massif.label: Besiberri Massif
Besiberri Massif.description: Besiberri Massif is a mountain massif of the central area of the Pyrenees, Lleida, Catalonia, Spain. It is located at the western limit of the Aigüestortes i Estany de Sant Maurici National Park. Wikipedia

Bifertenstock.label: Bifertenstock
Bifertenstock.description: The Bifertenstock is a mountain in the Glarus Alps, located between the cantons of Glarus and Graubünden. Wikipedia

Bilstein (Kaufunger Wald).label: Bilstein (Kaufunger Wald)
Bilstein (Kaufunger Wald).description: Bilstein is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Billingen.label: Billingen
Billingen.description: Billingen is the largest of the thirteen mesas in the Swedish county of Västra Götaland, with a maximum altitude of 299 metres. The mesa extends in a north-southerly direct with a length of 23 kilometres and a width of 11 kilometres. Wikipedia

Black Mesa (Oklahoma).label: Black Mesa
Black Mesa (Oklahoma).description: Black Mesa is a mesa in the U.S. states of Colorado, New Mexico, and Oklahoma. It extends from Mesa de Maya, Colorado southeasterly 28 miles along the north bank of the Cimarron River, crossing the ... Wikipedia
Black Mesa (Oklahoma).type: Mountain in United States of America

Beilstein (Spessart).label: Beilstein (Spessart)
Beilstein (Spessart).description: Beilstein is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Birkkarspitze.label: Birkkarspitze
Birkkarspitze.description: The Birkkarspitze is the highest mountain in the Karwendel range, Austria. It is located within the Innsbruck-Land District of Tyrol, Austria. Wikipedia

Blüemlisalp.label: Blüemlisalp
Blüemlisalp.description: The Blüemlisalp is a massif of the Bernese Alps, in the territory of the municipalities of Kandersteg and Reichenbach im Kandertal. Wikipedia

Blue Mountain Peak.label: Blue Mountain Peak
Blue Mountain Peak.description: Blue Mountain Peak is the highest mountain in Jamaica at 2,256 metres . It is the home of Blue Mountain coffee and their famous tours. Blue Mountain Peak is one of the highest peaks in the Caribbean. Wikipedia

Brünnstein.label: Brünnstein
Brünnstein.description: Brünnstein is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Borah Peak.label: Borah Peak
Borah Peak.description: Borah Peak is the highest mountain in the U.S. state of Idaho and one of the most prominent peaks in the contiguous states. It is located in the central section of the Lost River Range, within the Challis National Forest in eastern Custer County. Wikipedia

Brandberg Mountain.label: Brandberg Mountain
Brandberg Mountain.description: The Brandberg, is Namibia's highest mountain. Wikipedia

Breiteberg.label: Breiteberg
Breiteberg.description: The Breiteberg is a mountain in the Lausitzer Bergland in Free State of Saxony, Federal Republic of Germany, with an altitude of 510 metres above mean sea level. Wikipedia

Brend (mountain).label: Brend
Brend (mountain).description: Brend is a mountain of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Bruchberg.label: Bruchberg
Bruchberg.description: At 927 m above sea level the Bruchberg in the Upper Harz is the second highest mountain in Lower Saxony and the third highest in the Harz mountains in North Germany. It lies between Altenau and Torfhaus in the middle of the Harz National Park. Wikipedia

Buchschirm.label: Buchschirm
Buchschirm.description: Buchschirm is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Burgberg (Baunatal).label: Burgberg (Baunatal)
Burgberg (Baunatal).description: Burgberg is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. It is situated in the municipality Baunatal. Wikipedia

Castle Ring.label: Castle Ring
Castle Ring.description: Castle Ring is an Iron Age hill fort, situated high up on the southern edge of Cannock Chase, Staffordshire, in the village of Cannock Wood, England. Castle Ring was thought to have been occupied around AD 50, by the Celtic Cornovii tribe. Wikipedia

Central Breithorn.label: Central Breithorn
Central Breithorn.description: The Central Breithorn is a peak of the Breithorn massif in the Pennine Alps, located on the border between Switzerland and Italy, between the canton of Valais and the region of Aosta Valley. Wikipedia

Chacaltaya.label: Chacaltaya
Chacaltaya.description: Chacaltaya is a mountain in the Cordillera Real, one of the mountain ranges of the Cordillera Oriental, itself a range of the Bolivian Andes. Its elevation is 5,421 meters. Wikipedia

Chetco Peak.label: Chetco Peak
Chetco Peak.description: Chetco Peak is a mountain in the Klamath Mountains of southwestern Oregon in the United States. It is located in the southern Kalmiopsis Wilderness in southern Curry County in the extreme southwestern ... Wikipedia

Cheekha Dar.label: Cheekha Dar
Cheekha Dar.description: Cheekha Dar, or The Outer Row, is the local Kurdish name for the mountain currently thought to be the highest in Iraq. It is claimed to be 3,611 metres high in the CIA World Factbook. Wikipedia

Capelinhos.label: Capelinhos
Capelinhos.description: The Capelinhos is a monogenetic volcano located on the western coast of the island of Faial in the Azores. Wikipedia

Chopicalqui.label: Chopicalqui
Chopicalqui.description: Chopicalqui is a mountain in the Cordillera Blanca in the Andes of Peru. With a summit altitude of 6,354 meters above sea level it is one of the highest peaks of the Cordillera Blanca. Wikipedia

Churfirsten.label: Churfirsten
Churfirsten.description: Churfirsten is a mountain range in the Canton of St. Gallen, Switzerland. They form the natural boundary between the canton's Toggenburg and Sarganserland districts. Wikipedia

Cirspitzen.label: Pizes de Cir
Cirspitzen.description: The Pizes de Cir is a mountain range in South Tyrol, Italy. They are part of the Dolomites, north of Gardena Pass. The highest peak of this mountain range is the Gran Cir with an elevation of 2592 meter. Wikipedia

Collmberg.label: Collmberg
Collmberg.description: Collmberg is the highest elevation in the Nordsachsen district. Until the 19th Century it was also called Spielberg. Another early nomenclature was Oschatzer Collm. Wikipedia

Col di Lana.label: Col di Lana
Col di Lana.description: The Col di Lana is a mountain of the Fanes Group in the Italian Dolomites, situated in Livinallongo del Col di Lana, a municipality of the Province of Belluno, in the Italian region of Veneto. Wikipedia

Combin de la Tsessette.label: Combin de la Tsessette
Combin de la Tsessette.description: The Combin de la Tsessette is the third highest summit in the Grand Combin massif. It lies east of the Grand Combin summit and overlooks the Lac de Mauvoisin. Wikipedia

Corno Grande.label: Corno Grande
Corno Grande.description: Corno Grande is a peak situated in the central Italian province of Teramo in the Abruzzo region. It is part of the Gran Sasso massif in the Apennine Mountains and is the highest peak on the Italian Peninsula, at 2,912 m above sea level. Wikipedia

Bláhnjúkur.label: Bláhnjúkur
Bláhnjúkur.description:
Bláhnjúkur is a volcano in the south of Iceland. Its height is about 940 m.
Its name translates to blue peak in English. This comes from the blue-black colour of its sides. The colour is due to volcanic ash and lava flows. Wikipedia

Czorneboh.label: Czorneboh
Czorneboh.description: Czorneboh is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Dôme de Rochefort.label: Dôme de Rochefort
Dôme de Rochefort.description: The Dôme de Rochefort is a mountain in the Mont Blanc massif in Haute-Savoie, France and of Aosta Valley, Italy. Wikipedia

Dôme du Goûter.label: Dôme du Goûter
Dôme du Goûter.description: The Dôme du Goûter is a mountain in the Mont Blanc massif. It is a shoulder of Mont Blanc, whose summit lies two kilometres to the south-east. The Dôme is traversed on ascents of Mont Blanc via the Bosses route. Wikipedia

Dalsnibba.label: Dalsnibba
Dalsnibba.description: Dalsnibba is a mountain in Stranda Municipality in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. It is located at the end of the Geiranger valley, about 21 kilometres south of the village of Geiranger and the Geirangerfjorden. Wikipedia

Dammastock.label: Dammastock
Dammastock.description: The Dammastock is the highest mountain in the Urner Alps in Switzerland. Its summit ridge forms the border between the cantons of Uri and the Valais. It is the highest summit in the canton of Uri. Wikipedia

Dammersfeldkuppe.label: Dammersfeldkuppe
Dammersfeldkuppe.description: At 927.9 m above sea level the Dammersfeldkuppe in Bavaria is the second highest mountain after the Wasserkuppe in the Rhön, a low mountain range straddling the states of Bavaria, Hesse and Thuringia in Germany. Wikipedia

Dürrenstein (South Tyrol).label: Dürrenstein
Dürrenstein (South Tyrol).description: The Dürrenstein is a mountain in the Dolomites in South Tyrol, Italy. Wikipedia

Devínska Kobyla.label: Devínska Kobyla
Devínska Kobyla.description: Devínska Kobyla is the highest peak in the Devín Carpathians, part of the Little Carpathians mountain range, and the highest point of Bratislava, the capital of Slovakia. Wikipedia

Diablerets.label: Les Diablerets
Diablerets.description:
Les Diablerets is a village and ski resort located in the municipality of Ormont-Dessus in the canton of Vaud, Switzerland.
The village lies at an altitude of 1,160 metres on the north side of the massif of the Diablerets in the Swiss Alps. Wikipedia

Didi Abuli.label: Didi Abuli
Didi Abuli.description: Didi Abuli is one of the highest peak of the Lesser Caucasus Mountains in the nation of Georgia. The mountain is located in the Abul-Samsari Range at an elevation of 3,300 m above sea level. Wikipedia

Doldenhorn.label: Doldenhorn
Doldenhorn.description: The Doldenhorn is a mountain of the Bernese Alps, overlooking Kandersteg in the Bernese Oberland. On its northern side is located Lake Oeschinen. Wikipedia

Demeljoch.label: Demeljoch
Demeljoch.description: The Demeljoch is a mountain at the border between Bavaria, Germany and Tyrol, Austria. The summit can be reached through a hiking trail starting near the easternmost point of the Sylvensteinsee. Wikipedia

Drachenkopf bei Nassau.label: Drachenkopf
Drachenkopf bei Nassau.description: Drachenkopf bei Nassau is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Dreiländerspitze.label: Dreiländerspitze
Dreiländerspitze.description: The Dreiländerspitze is one of the higher mountains in the Silvretta range in the eastern Alps, at 3,197 metres. The borders of Graubünden, Vorarlberg and Tyrol meet at the peak. Wikipedia

Dyleň.label: Dyleň
Dyleň.description: Dyleň is a mountain in the Karlovy Vary Region of western Bohemia, located roughly 100 metres from the Czech Republic–Germany border. At 939 metres above sea level, its summit is the second highest peak in the Upper Palatinate Range. Wikipedia

Dylewska Góra.label: Dylewska Góra
Dylewska Góra.description: Dylewska Góra is a mountain located in northeastern Poland, south of the town of Ostróda, in the Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship. With elevation of 312 m above sea level, it is one of the highest peaks of northern and central Poland. Wikipedia

Dzyarzhynskaya Hara.label: Dzyarzhynskaya Hara
Dzyarzhynskaya Hara.description: Dzyarzhynskaya hara is the highest point in Belarus. The hill is 345 meters above sea level and is located west of Minsk, near Dzyarzhynsk, in the village Skirmuntava. The original name of the hill was Svyataya hara. Wikipedia

Eagle Peak (Wyoming).label: Eagle Peak
Eagle Peak (Wyoming).description: Eagle Peak is a mountain in the Absaroka Range in the U.S. state of Wyoming and at 11,372 feet is the highest point in Yellowstone National Park. It is located about 6 miles east of the southeast arm of Yellowstone Lake. Wikipedia

Ehrenbürg.label: Ehrenbürg
Ehrenbürg.description: The Ehrenbürg is a double-peaked butte on the edge of the Franconian Jura in Bavaria, Germany. It is in the district of Forchheim in Upper Franconia, in the municipalities of Kirchehrenbach, Leutenbach and Wiesenthau. Wikipedia

El Chichón.label: El Chichón
El Chichón.description: El Chichón, also known as Chichonal, is an active volcano in Francisco León, north-western Chiapas, Mexico. El Chichón is part of a geologic zone known as the Chiapanecan Volcanic Arc. Wikipedia

Emi Koussi.label: Emi Koussi
Emi Koussi.description: Emi Koussi is a high pyroclastic shield volcano that lies at the south end of the Tibesti Mountains in the central Sahara of northern Chad. It is the highest mountain in Chad, and the highest in the Sahara. Wikipedia

Entenbühl.label: Entenbühl
Entenbühl.description: Entenbühl is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Essigberg.label: Essigberg
Essigberg.description: Essigberg is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Farrenberg.label: Farrenberg
Farrenberg.description: Farrenberg is a mountain of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Finsteraarhorn.label: Finsteraarhorn
Finsteraarhorn.description: The Finsteraarhorn is the highest mountain in the Bernese Alps and the highest mountain in the canton of Berne. It is also the highest summit in the Alps lying outside the main chain, or watershed. Wikipedia

Firnskuppe.label: Firnskuppe
Firnskuppe.description: Firnskuppe is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Flüela Schwarzhorn.label: Flüela Schwarzhorn
Flüela Schwarzhorn.description: The Flüela Schwarzhorn is a mountain of the Albula Alps, overlooking the Flüela Pass, in the canton of Graubünden. With a height of 3,146 metres above sea level, it is the highest point of the Albula Alps north of the Fuorcla da Grialetsch. Wikipedia

Fockeberg.label: Fockeberg
Fockeberg.description: Fockeberg is a Schuttberg in the south of Leipzig Saxony, southeastern Germany, and is actually a pile of rubble left over from the bombing during World War II. Wikipedia

Frauenkopf.label: Frauenkopf
Frauenkopf.description: Frauenkopf is a mountain of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Fukutoku-Okanoba.label: Fukutoku-Okanoba
Fukutoku-Okanoba.description: Fukutoku-Okanoba is a submarine volcano that is part of the Volcano Islands in the Bonin Islands of Japan. It is located 5 kilometers northeast of the island of South Iwo Jima. Wikipedia
